pl.sii.nnv.parse

Class ParseGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.sii.nnv.parse.ParseGraph

  • public class ParseGraph
extends java.lang.Object
    ParseGraph contains methods to process graph objects from Caffe and Tensorflow.

    The methods includes:

    • Reading graph from .proto input (text and binary)
    • Writing graph to .proto output (text and binary)
    • Mapping graph to inner MappedRoot structure
    • Processing of the nodes

      • addRecursive

        public static void addRecursive(MappedRoot obj,
                                java.lang.String[] name,
                                int depth)
        Recursively checks if the given node name is added to the root MappedRoot list. If not it adds the node to the list based on the parents nodes.
        Parameters:
        obj - Object of type MappedRoot being assembled by parser
        name - Name of the node under processing
        depth - Recursive depth of processing.
